      "side": 1,
      "message": "In py-bb, validate_update_build_request() validates \"build.outout.properties\" with validate_struct(), which simply checks all the Value objects are instance of the supported value types.\nhttps://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:appengine/cr-buildbucket/validation.py;l\u003d258-261\n\nHowever looking at https://github.com/protocolbuffers/protobuf-go/blob/v1.25.0/types/known/structpb/struct.pb.go#L318, struct_pb.go doesn\u0027t allow any uninitialized Value at all. If the Value object was nil, then NewValue() creates and assigns NullValue{}.\n\nI don\u0027t the same validation makes sense for golang, and skipped porting validate_struct().\nLet me know if this is not correct.",
